                        <rect x="0" y="0" width="100%" height="100%" fill="transparent" stroke="white" stroke-width="1px" rx="24px" ry="24px"></rect>
                      </mask>
                    </defs>
                  </svg>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBorder__tpcau"></div>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBody__o2PZ2">
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemHeader__AWP1r">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemQuestion__hdGN7">Is it possible to receive payment early?</div>
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggle__xoJYp">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggleBg__Omqef"></div><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                          <path stroke="#fff" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="m4 8 6 6 6-6"></path>
                        </svg>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsible__Y1Ces">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsibleInner__Ln6PE">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswer__HGfEd">Yes, this option is discussed individually with your personal manager.<br /><br />However, it is important to understand that early payments are possible provided the traffic quality is consistently high and volumes are large.</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="FaqPage_faqItem__inLMu" style="--mask-value:url(#:Rb7pusltrb:)"><svg class="FaqPage_faqItemBorderMask__PjztE" width="0" height="0">
                    <defs>
                      <mask id=":Rb7pusltrb:">
                        <rect x="0" y="0" width="100%" height="100%" fill="transparent" stroke="white" stroke-width="1px" rx="24px" ry="24px"></rect>
                      </mask>
                    </defs>
                  </svg>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBorder__tpcau"></div>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBody__o2PZ2">
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemHeader__AWP1r">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemQuestion__hdGN7">Is it possible to increase the rate?</div>
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggle__xoJYp">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggleBg__Omqef"></div><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                          <path stroke="#fff" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="m4 8 6 6 6-6"></path>
                        </svg>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsible__Y1Ces">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsibleInner__Ln6PE">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswer__HGfEd">We always go to meet our trusted partners who attract quality traffic. Rate increases are provided for them. High traffic volume, with high quality, is the main reason for increasing the rate.</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="FaqPage_faqItem__inLMu" style="--mask-value:url(#:Rd7pusltrb:)"><svg class="FaqPage_faqItemBorderMask__PjztE" width="0" height="0">
                    <defs>
                      <mask id=":Rd7pusltrb:">
                        <rect x="0" y="0" width="100%" height="100%" fill="transparent" stroke="white" stroke-width="1px" rx="24px" ry="24px"></rect>
                      </mask>
                    </defs>
                  </svg>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBorder__tpcau"></div>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBody__o2PZ2">
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemHeader__AWP1r">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemQuestion__hdGN7">What is hold?</div>
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggle__xoJYp">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggleBg__Omqef"></div><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                          <path stroke="#fff" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="m4 8 6 6 6-6"></path>
                        </svg>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsible__Y1Ces">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsibleInner__Ln6PE">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswer__HGfEd">Hold is a period of time during which the quality of traffic attracted by the webmaster is analyzed, as well as additional checks by the anti-fraud system. The hold period may vary depending on the terms of the offer and may be increased if fraud is suspected.<br /><br />Confirmed leads will be paid according to the affiliate program payment schedule.</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="FaqPage_faqItem__inLMu" style="--mask-value:url(#:Rf7pusltrb:)"><svg class="FaqPage_faqItemBorderMask__PjztE" width="0" height="0">
                    <defs>
                      <mask id=":Rf7pusltrb:">
                        <rect x="0" y="0" width="100%" height="100%" fill="transparent" stroke="white" stroke-width="1px" rx="24px" ry="24px"></rect>
                      </mask>
                    </defs>
                  </svg>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBorder__tpcau"></div>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBody__o2PZ2">
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemHeader__AWP1r">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemQuestion__hdGN7">What is the difference between CPA and Revenue Share?</div>
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggle__xoJYp">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggleBg__Omqef"></div><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                          <path stroke="#fff" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="m4 8 6 6 6-6"></path>
                        </svg>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsible__Y1Ces">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsibleInner__Ln6PE">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswer__HGfEd">RS (Revenue Share) is a payment model in which the affiliate receives a percentage of the amount deposited or lost by the user attracted via his referral link.<br /><br />CPA (Cost Per Action) is a payment model in which the affiliate receives a fixed amount for the user&#x27;s target action performed via his referral link.</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="FaqPage_faqItem__inLMu" style="--mask-value:url(#:Rh7pusltrb:)"><svg class="FaqPage_faqItemBorderMask__PjztE" width="0" height="0">
                    <defs>
                      <mask id=":Rh7pusltrb:">
                        <rect x="0" y="0" width="100%" height="100%" fill="transparent" stroke="white" stroke-width="1px" rx="24px" ry="24px"></rect>
                      </mask>
                    </defs>
                  </svg>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBorder__tpcau"></div>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBody__o2PZ2">
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemHeader__AWP1r">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemQuestion__hdGN7">What is SOI, DOI?</div>
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggle__xoJYp">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggleBg__Omqef"></div><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                          <path stroke="#fff" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="m4 8 6 6 6-6"></path>
                        </svg>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsible__Y1Ces">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsibleInner__Ln6PE">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswer__HGfEd">SOI (Single Opt-In) and DOI (Double Opt-In) are models for confirming user subscriptions.<br /><br />SOI (Single Opt-In) — the user leaves their data, such as email or phone number, and automatically becomes a subscriber, without requiring additional confirmation.<br /><br />DOI (Double Opt-In) — after entering the data, the user must confirm their subscription, for example, by clicking on a link in an email. This model provides higher-quality and targeted leads, since the user confirms their desire to receive content or services with their action.</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="FaqPage_faqItem__inLMu" style="--mask-value:url(#:Rj7pusltrb:)"><svg class="FaqPage_faqItemBorderMask__PjztE" width="0" height="0">
                    <defs>
                      <mask id=":Rj7pusltrb:">
                        <rect x="0" y="0" width="100%" height="100%" fill="transparent" stroke="white" stroke-width="1px" rx="24px" ry="24px"></rect>
                      </mask>
                    </defs>
                  </svg>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBorder__tpcau"></div>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBody__o2PZ2">
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemHeader__AWP1r">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemQuestion__hdGN7">What is KPI?</div>
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggle__xoJYp">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggleBg__Omqef"></div><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                          <path stroke="#fff" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="m4 8 6 6 6-6"></path>
                        </svg>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsible__Y1Ces">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsibleInner__Ln6PE">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswer__HGfEd">KPI (Key Performance Indicators) are the advertiser&#x27;s requirements for traffic, which are used to assess its quality and payback. The conditions under which traffic will be paid are specified in each offer.<br /><br />Fulfillment of the established KPIs can affect the improvement of cooperation conditions, such as the size of payments, access to exclusive offers or the provision of additional bonuses.</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="FaqPage_faqItem__inLMu" style="--mask-value:url(#:Rl7pusltrb:)"><svg class="FaqPage_faqItemBorderMask__PjztE" width="0" height="0">
                    <defs>
                      <mask id=":Rl7pusltrb:">
                        <rect x="0" y="0" width="100%" height="100%" fill="transparent" stroke="white" stroke-width="1px" rx="24px" ry="24px"></rect>
                      </mask>
                    </defs>
                  </svg>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBorder__tpcau"></div>
                  <div class="FaqPage_faqItemBody__o2PZ2">
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemHeader__AWP1r">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemQuestion__hdGN7">What is the test limit (Cap)?</div>
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggle__xoJYp">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemToggleBg__Omqef"></div><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                          <path stroke="#fff" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="m4 8 6 6 6-6"></path>
                        </svg>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsible__Y1Ces">
                      <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswerCollapsibleInner__Ln6PE">
                        <div class="FaqPage_faqItemAnswer__HGfEd">When you first start working with any offer, you need to pass the qualification so that your traffic is recognized by the advertiser as high-quality. To do this, you need to bring a limited number of conversions to the offer in test mode - they are called a test limit.<br /><br />When the test limit is reached, you need to stop the traffic and inform your personal manager about it.<br /><br />If your traffic is approved, a payment will be scheduled for it in the next week. Then, after agreement with the advertiser, you can launch advertising campaigns again.</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="FaqPage_faqGroup__kO1dC">
              <div class="FaqPage_faqGroupTitle__0bJb_">Technical questions</div>
